  "description": "Apex switch-on-SObjectType patterns \u2014 type dispatching across SObject collections, polymorphic handlers, the typed-variable binding that makes `when SObjectType varName` more than a tag check. Covers the single-type-per-when-block restriction, the null branch, the no-fall-through rule, and why `Type.forName()` cannot be used in a switch expression. NOT for basic Apex switch syntax on Integer / String / enum (use Apex Developer Guide directly), NOT for dynamic field access (see apex/dynamic-apex).",
